Commentary Text: Boult to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Rutherford!! Riyan Parag will find the fielder. He is disappointed with himself. But cheer up young man, you have just played a special innings for your team. It was on a fuller length again, Riyan Parag wanted to dispatch it over long-off, he wasn't balanced at the point of contact. And lost his shape, it comes off the bottom half of the willow and Rutherford makes no mistake at long-off. Riyan Parag c Rutherford b Boult 50(49) [4s-4 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Boult to Riyan Parag, SIX, gets his maiden IPL fifty in style with a maximum. He becomes the youngest cricketer in the IPL to score a fifty!  Gee! This young man has some power. And he has flaunted that on this delivery. It was in the slot on a fuller length, he swings his willow, gets it off the sweet spot and it went a long way back into the stands. And boy, isn't he pumped!

Commentary Text: Mishra to Gowtham, 1 run, oh dear! Would you believe it! Trent Boult has denied Amit Mishra his fourth hat-trick in the IPL. And he would be absolutely gutted. It was a well flighted wrong 'un, Gowtham bends down low and goes for an almighty heave. It comes off the top half of the bat and was in the air for a long time. Two men called for it, one was Boult and the other was Rutherford. Perhaps that put the former off, he misjudged it completely and then had to jump back to complete the catch - can't grab hold of the ball and Mishra has his hands on his head

Golden duck for Binny!Binny c Pant b Mishra 0(1)

Commentary Text: Axar to Samson, out Samson Run Out!! Oh dear! This is disaster for the Royals - zero communication from both batsman - Lomror kept screaming at his partner who was oblivious to his call, kept running down the track aand then had nowhere to go. This was tossed up on off and Samson pushed it towards cover-point, he took a step down the track and stopped, so did his partner and then suddenly Samson had this urge to run - kept running even as his partner asked him to go back. All Shaw had to do was to pick the ball and throw to the kepeer - he does better and finds the stumps with a direct hit. Samson run out (Prithvi Shaw) 5(8)

Commentary Text: Ishant to Rahane, out Caught by Dhawan!! That's a soft dismissal for the captain - a leg-stump half-volley from Ishant, Rahane was looking to work it to the on-side, closed the bat-face early, gets a fat leading edge, high and behind square on the on-side. Dhawan called for the catch, gets across from deep backward square leg, watches the ball all along and completes the catch - cuts to his trademark thighslap celebrations, the Royals have lost an easrly wicket. Rahane c Dhawan b Ishant 2(4)

Commentary Text: Ish Sodhi to Ingram, out Caught by Rahane!! And when Pant's extravaganza doesn't consume him, Ingram's cheek will. So he tries to be cute, with a late fine sweep past the keeper. But in his pre-guessing, gets a little too early into it and the length's just too full for it as well, resulting in a glove, popping up off his shoulder to a very-alert Rahane - at slip - who runs to where a leg-slip would've been.
